Los tonos son baratos
Para los que los usan son baratos, y están dispuestos a pagar mas por ellos, pero no por una canción completa. Curioso.

<blockquote>
<p><a href="http://blogs.zdnet.com/ITFacts/?p=9941" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink"> Ringtones at $2.50 a pop under-valued</a> by <a href="http://zdnet.com">ZDNet</a>'s ZDNet Research -- According to The NPD Group,, consumers are willing to pay more for a 30-second snippet of a song track to be used as a ringtone than to download an entire song track. In addition, consumers are willing to pay a premium (above the average $0.99 price for paid music downloads from the Web) for the [...]</p>
